a-register_action="community_reply">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies top_level_replies"><div data-post="{&quot;user_id&quot;:8026680,&quot;id&quot;:8902817}" class="community_post is_reply has_vote_column" id="post-8902817"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjesse-m.itch.io%2Fjungle-pack&amp;intent=community" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn" title="Vote up" data-register_action="community_vote"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden version="1.1" height="20" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" role="img" width="20"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjesse-m.itch.io%2Fjungle-pack&amp;intent=community" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn" title="Vote down" data-register_action="community_vote"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden version="1.1" height="20" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" role="img" width="20"><polygon points="2 6 12 18 22 6" /></svg></a></div><a href="https://itch.io/profile/eytelis" class="avatar_container"><div style="background-image: url(/static/images/frog.png)" class="post_avatar"></div></a><div class="post_header"><span class="post_author"><a href="https://itch.io/profile/eytelis">eytelis</a></span><span title="2023-11-19 10:57:47" class="post_date"><a href="https://itch.io/post/8902817">2 years ago</a></span><span class="vote_counts"></span></div><div class="post_content"><div dir="auto" class="post_body user_formatted"><p>it&#x27;s very unlikely you still need help, but in case you do: search for &quot;paralax background&quot; tutorials. Basically, the paralax effect means that objects closer to you move slower than those further away. That&#x27;s why there are layers</p></div><div class="post_footer"><a class="post_action reply_btn" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Fjesse-m.itch.io%2Fjungle-pack&amp;intent=community" data-register_action="community_reply">Reply</a></div></div></